folder: Flatbush Avenue & Linden Boulevard, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Flatbush Ave., no: th from Linden Boulevard.
June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Flatbush Avenue & Linden Boulevard, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Flatbush Ave., south from Linden Boulevard; a view of the Flatbush Trust Co. This same building, with architectural changes, now houses the American Exchange Irving Trust Co.

About 1908.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing a more general view of the Ave., with the afre mentioned building at the left.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing a closer view, after being remodeled.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Flatbush Avenue & Linden Boulevard, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Flatbush Ave., east side, between Linden Boulevard and Martense Street. In background, are rears of frame homes facing on East 21st Street; between them is the top of the Union League Club.
January 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, from a slightly different angle.
January 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
